✅ Task: Automate Code Deployment Using CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub Actions)
📌 Project Title
Simple Node.js App with CI/CD using GitHub Actions and Docker

📁 Project Description
This project demonstrates the implementation of a CI/CD pipeline using GitHub Actions to automate the build and deployment process of a simple Node.js web application. The application is packaged using Docker and pushed to Docker Hub as part of the CI/CD workflow.

🎯 Objectives
Create a basic Node.js web app.

Containerize the application using Docker.

Set up a GitHub repository and configure GitHub Actions workflow.

Automate Docker image build and push to Docker Hub on every push to the main branch.

